{
  "stem": "26142.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And in that city, there is a Judenrat there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And there are thousands of Jews live in that city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And they are taking-- taking care of-- of Hungarian refugees.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And he said-- this was four days before Rosh Hashanah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Rosh Hashanah usually starts September.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And don't forget, we-- we left August the 3rd.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And-- and the reason why I remember that, I-- I'll-- I'll skip it now.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I remember it, because we want to go-- get ahead a little bit.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "He said, before Rosh Hashanah, I will come to see you-- to see you on the other side of the Dniester River, yet.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I just want to mention now, when I came to the United States, first thing I did was I put in an ad in the-- in the [NON-ENGLISH] journal, the-- the-- the daily newspaper that appeared in New York City and under forward-- asking people if they know the man, Isaak Zummer, from that and that area-- if he survived.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Sadly, I never got any answer or anybody that knows.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I'm not finished with him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Exactly we told the-- the-- the-- people that we stayed-- that widow-- and her daughter and son-in-law-- we told them what happened to us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And we told them that Isaak Zummer hired somebody.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And did-- she-- they assured us if Isaak Zummer did, then you rest assure, he has-- he has reliable people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Exactly around 12 o'clock at night, the man came.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the-- the week before Rosh Hashanah, it is customary for Jews, religious Jews, to say [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did you hear the word, [NON-ENGLISH]?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where you get up early, be early into the synagogue, say [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In this widow's house, they had one room, so the-- and there was one bed in the room.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
